  "title": "Autocomplete widget requires React 18 but peerDependencies allow 16.8+",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\n`react-instantsearch@7.18.0+` declares peer dependencies of `\"react\": \">= 16.8.0 < 20\"`, but the `Autocomplete` widget imports `useId` directly from React, which is only available in React 18+.\n\nThis causes build failures for projects using React 17:\n```\nERROR in ./node_modules/react-instantsearch/dist/es/widgets/Autocomplete.js\nexport 'useId' (imported as 'useId') was not found in 'react'\n```\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. create a project with React 17.x\n2. install `react-instantsearch@7.18.0` or later\n3. build with webpack (or any bundler that processes `node_modules`)\n4. build should fail (even if `Autocomplete` is not directly used) because bundlers process the entire package\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nn/a\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\n`peerDependencies` should reflect actual React version requirements, or `useId` should be shimmed for backwards compatibility\n\n### Package version\n\nreact-instantsearch@7.18.0+\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
